geogcomments: The new primate fossils occur in the Solimoes Formation at Patos, along the upper Acre River (10° 55' 55" S, 69° 550' 20" W) in a riverbank cut approximately 38 km upriver from the towns of Assis (on the Brazilian side) and Inapari (on the Peruvian side) (Fig. 1).
